<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-GB">
  <!-- @import "../head" -->
  <body>
    <!-- @import "../header" -->

    <main class="article-page quick-win">
      <!-- BREADCRUMB -->
      <div class="breadcrumb">
        <span class="tag tag-yellow-light">QUICK WIN</span>
        <span class="read-time-badge">5 MIN READ</span>
      </div>

      <!-- ARTICLE TITLE + AUTHOR -->
      <h1>The 3-Click Figma Component Swap</h1>
      <div class="article-author">
        <img src="../assets/img/gui.avif" alt="Gui" class="avatar" />
        <div class="article-author-info">
          <p class="author-name">By Guilherme</p>
          <p class="author-date">Published June 12, 2026</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- TWO-COLUMN LAYOUT -->
      <div class="article-layout">
        <!-- MAIN CONTENT COLUMN -->
        <article class="article-content">
          <blockquote class="intro-quote">
            Stop manually detaching instances. This keyboard shortcut swaps
            components globally without breaking auto-layout — and it works
            across frames, pages, and nested groups.
          </blockquote>

          <h2 id="1-selectYourInstance">1. Select Your Instance</h2>
          <p>
            Click any component instance on your canvas. You don't need to enter
            the group or select individual layers — the top-level instance is
            all you need. Hold <strong>Cmd</strong> (Mac) or
            <strong>Ctrl</strong> (Windows) if you want to multi-select
            instances of different variants at once.
          </p>

          <pre class="code-block"><code>/* Keyboard shortcut */
Right-click → "Swap component" (or)
Right Panel → Component → Swap icon ⇄</code></pre>

          <h2 id="2-openTheSwapPanel">2. Open the Swap Panel</h2>
          <p>
            With the instance selected, look at the right panel under the
            component header. Click the <strong>swap icon (⇄)</strong> next to
            the component name. This opens a searchable picker showing every
            component in your local file and any published libraries you have
            enabled.
          </p>

          <div class="video-embed">
            <img
              src="../assets/img/video-thumb.jpg"
              alt="Component swap demo"
            />
          </div>

          <h2 id="3-pickAndConfirm">3. Pick and Confirm</h2>
          <p>
            Type to filter, hover to preview, then click to swap. Figma
            intelligently maps matching property names — so if both components
            share a <code>size</code> or <code>state</code> property, those
            values carry over automatically. Auto-layout constraints and spacing
            are preserved throughout.
          </p>

          <blockquote class="pull-quote">
            "The swap panel isn't just a time-saver — it's the cleanest way to
            A/B test component variants across an entire flow without touching a
            single override."
          </blockquote>

          <p>
            This also works in bulk: select multiple mismatched instances, open
            the swap panel, and Figma will replace all of them with your chosen
            component in one shot. No detaching, no re-applying styles, no
            broken constraints.
          </p>

          <div class="article-tags">
            <span>Figma</span>
            <span>Components</span>
            <span>Auto Layout</span>
            <span>Workflow</span>
          </div>

          <!-- CTA BANNER -->
          <div class="article-cta">
            <h3>Found this useful?</h3>
            <p>Got a workflow hack of your own? Share it with the community.</p>
            <a href="../contact.html" class="btn btn-light">SUGGEST A TIP →</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <!-- SIDEBAR -->
        <aside class="article-sidebar">
          <!-- TOC Widget -->
          <div class="sidebar-widget">
            <h4 class="sidebar-title">Article Guide</h4>
            <p class="sidebar-label">Quick Navigation</p>
            <nav class="toc">
              <a href="#1-selectYourInstance" class="toc-active"
                >Select Your Instance</a
              >
              <a href="#2-openTheSwapPanel" class="toc-link"
                >Open the Swap Panel</a
              >
              <a href="#3-pickAndConfirm" class="toc-link">Pick and Confirm</a>
            </nav>
          </div>

          <!-- Pro Tip Callout -->
          <div class="sidebar-tip">
            <div class="sidebar-tip-label">
              <span>PRO TIP</span>
            </div>
            <p>
              Hold <strong>Option</strong> (Mac) or <strong>Alt</strong>
              (Windows) while swapping to keep all overrides — text, colours,
              and nested instances — intact on the new component.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Related Resources -->
          <div class="sidebar-related">
            <p class="sidebar-label sidebar-label--spaced">RELATED RESOURCES</p>
            <a
              href="../articles/building-design-system.html"
              class="related-card"
            >
              <p class="related-card-title">
                Building a Design Token System from Scratch
              </p>
              <span class="related-card-link">Read More →</span>
            </a>
            <a href="../articles/12-Font-Pairings.html" class="related-card">
              <p class="related-card-title">
                The 12 Font Pairings That Always Work
              </p>
              <span class="related-card-link">Read More →</span>
            </a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
      <!-- end .article-layout -->
    </main>

    <!-- @import "../footer" -->
  </body>
</html>
